         <OBJECT_CONTRACT>
            <TITLE>
               <P>United Kingdom — Broxbourne School: School building works and housing development</P>
            </TITLE>
            <CPV_MAIN>
               <CPV_CODE CODE="45214220"/>
            </CPV_MAIN>
            <TYPE_CONTRACT CTYPE="WORKS"/>
            <SHORT_DESCR>
               <P>Broxbourne School intends to enter into an agreement with Chase new homes limited for the sale of some of its land (the School having obtained Secretary of State consent to sell) and development on that land of school buildings and residential housing. The new school buildings are to form part of the consideration for the land. The transaction aggregates the land sale, new school building works, and housing development into a single transaction.</P>
            </SHORT_DESCR>
            <VAL_TOTAL CURRENCY="GBP">40000000.00</VAL_TOTAL>
            <NO_LOT_DIVISION/>
            <OBJECT_DESCR ITEM="1">
               <CPV_ADDITIONAL>
                  <CPV_CODE CODE="45111291"/>
               </CPV_ADDITIONAL>
               <CPV_ADDITIONAL>
                  <CPV_CODE CODE="45211300"/>
               </CPV_ADDITIONAL>
               <n2016:NUTS CODE="UKH23"/>
               <MAIN_SITE>
                  <P>Broxbourne School.</P>
                  <P>High Rd Broxbourne.</P>
                  <P>Broxbourne.</P>
                  <P>EN10 7DD.</P>
               </MAIN_SITE>
               <SHORT_DESCR>
                  <P>The School selected Chase new homes limited after satisfying itself that Article 32(2)(a) (no suitable tenders and initial conditions of the contract have not been substantially altered) and (c) (extreme urgency due to unforeseeable events) apply and that therefore a contract may be awarded via use of the negotiated procedure without prior publication.</P>
               </SHORT_DESCR>
               <NO_OPTIONS/>
               <NO_EU_PROGR_RELATED/>
            </OBJECT_DESCR>
         </OBJECT_CONTRACT>
         <PROCEDURE>
            <DIRECTIVE_2014_24_EU>
               <PT_NEGOTIATED_WITHOUT_PUBLICATION>
                  <D_ACCORDANCE_ARTICLE>
                     <D_PROC_RESTRICTED/>
                     <D_EXTREME_URGENCY/>
                  </D_ACCORDANCE_ARTICLE>
                  <D_JUSTIFICATION>
                     <P>The School selected Chase new homes limited after satisfying itself that Article 32(2)(a) and (c) apply.</P>
                     <P>32(2)(a) — no suitable tenders and initial conditions of the contract have not been substantially altered. The School had previously appointed a Preferred framework member, but that member was unable to maintain its tender position due to its inability to conclude funding, sub-contract, or build within the price tendered. The School then entered discussions with its reserve Preferred framework member, which also failed to agree terms with its sub-contractors and could not proceed. The School is of the view that there is significant risk of a lack of credible market response given the risk profile required by the School.</P>
                     <P>32(2)(c) — extreme urgency due to unforeseeable events. As a result of the delays in procurement highlighted above, the project is already delayed by a year to September 2020 and any further delay will mean it will be very challenging for the School to enable Hertfordshire County Council to meet its statutory obligations to provide pupil places in this area of Hertfordshire. Furthermore, the planning consent was awarded in April 2017 and will expire in April 2019 and a fresh tender exercise would make meeting that deadline extremely unlikely. The School has already incurred significant cost in procurement and a new tender exercise would require significant investment without any certainty of outcome.</P>
                  </D_JUSTIFICATION>
               </PT_NEGOTIATED_WITHOUT_PUBLICATION>
            </DIRECTIVE_2014_24_EU>
